The paper discusses techniques for compressing the inverted index, which is a core data structure used in large-scale search engines. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of compression to improve query processing and reduce storage requirements, which are topics that are relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), and Computer Networks and Communications (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses experimentation and performance evaluation, which are topics that are relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
